7. Project Structure
diabetic_retinopathy_project/       ← Project root (run manage.py from here)
│
├── dr_project/                    ← Django project package
│   ├── __init__.py                ← Makes it a Python package
│   ├── settings.py                ← ALL configuration (DB, apps, paths)
│   ├── urls.py                    ← Main URL router
│   └── wsgi.py                    ← Production server entry point
│
├── detection/                     ← Our main app (DR detection logic)
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── admin.py                   ← Django admin configuration
│   ├── forms.py                   ← HTML form definitions
│   ├── models.py                  ← Database tables (Patient, Result, Profile)
│   ├── urls.py                    ← App-level URL patterns
│   ├── views.py                   ← Page logic / controllers
│   ├── migrations/                ← Auto-generated database migrations
│   └── ml_model/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── predictor.py           ← ResNet50 + Grad-CAM inference engine
│       └── dr_model.pth           ← Trained model weights (you add this)
│
├── templates/                     ← HTML templates
│   └── detection/
│       ├── add_patient.html       ← Add patient form 
│       ├── analyze.html           ← Image upload + scan form
│       ├── base.html              ← Master layout (navbar, footer)
│       ├── dashboard.html         ← Main dashboard with charts
│       ├── edit_patient.html      ← Edit patient form
│       ├── history.html           ← Full scan history
│       ├── home.html              ← Public landing page
│       ├── login.html             ← Doctor login page
│       ├── patient_detail.html    ← One patient's history
│       ├── patient_list.html      ← All patients
│       ├── profile.html           ← Doctor profile page
│       ├── register.html          ← Doctor registration
│       └── result_detail.html     ← AI result + heatmap view 
│
├── manage.py                      ← Django's command-line tool
├── requirements.txt               ← Python dependencies
└── db.sqlite3                     ← SQLite database (auto-created)


8. Run Your Program:
python manage.py makemigrations detection
- `makemigrations` → Django reads your models.py and creates migration files
  (blueprint files that describe what database tables to create)

python manage.py migrate
- `migrate` → Django reads those blueprint files and actually creates the tables
  in db.sqlite3

python manage.py runserver
Open: http://127.0.0.1:8000  ← Note: Django uses port 8000

